description:
&lt;p&gt;East Cheshire NHS Trust is seeking a Communications and Engagement Officer to support the communications and engagement team in the delivery of the internal and external communications and engagement strategy with focus on statutory public information disclosures through the Freedom of Information (FOI) process.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The role will also encompass the co-ordination of key patient information delivered to the public through effective use of digital and print methods.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This post is Permanent&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Hours per week: 28&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Closing date: 10th November 2020&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;To keep up to date with all of our latest Recruitment activity here at East Cheshire NHS Trust, take a look at our Careers website with lots of information on how to join our team and Facebook and Twitter pages, links to which can be found on the right hand side:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Visit our Facebook page: Careers at East Cheshire NHS Trust&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Follow us on Twitter: @CareersECT&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Name Suzanne Baker Job title Media &amp; Communications Manager Email address suzanne.baker4@nhs.net Telephone number 01625 663935&lt;/p&gt;
